POSTURE B LEAK SCAN
============================================================
Command: find dist/building/multi-tenancy -name '*.html' -exec grep -l 'source:' {} ;
Result: dist/building/multi-tenancy/index.html FOUND — 35 occurrences
Posture B assumption VIOLATED.

Root cause: HTML comments embedded inside Markdown table cell content and inside Starlight
  `:::note`/`:::caution` directive blocks ARE passed through to the HTML output by the
  Astro/Starlight/remark Markdown pipeline. Standalone HTML comments between block elements
  (paragraph-level) are also preserved in the HTML as HTML comments (which browsers don't
  display but which ARE present in the source).

Scope: This is a systemic issue — find dist -name '*.html' -exec grep -l 'source:' {} ;
  returns 10+ pages. Phase 02 "248/248 clean" Posture B claim was incorrect.

This page has THREE distinct leak modes:
  1. Citations inside Markdown table cells (e.g., table rows at page lines 12-18)
     → rendered inline as visible HTML comments inside <td> content
  2. Citations inside `:::note`/`:::caution` directive blocks (e.g., page line 127)
     → rendered inside the <aside> component's paragraph content
  3. Standalone HTML comments between paragraphs (e.g., page lines 24, 45, 49-50, etc.)
     → rendered as HTML comments in the output (<!-- ... --> preserved)

Mode 3 (standalone between-paragraph comments) is invisible in browsers since HTML comments
are not rendered. Modes 1 and 2 are also HTML comments (<!-- --> form), so they are
invisible to end users, but they ARE in the source that search engines, screen readers,
and Pagefind index. Pagefind evidence: bun run build outputs "281 HTML files" indexed.

The Writer should be directed to move table-cell and directive-block citations to standalone
lines between paragraphs, OR the methodology should accept that <!-- --> comments in HTML
are non-rendering and not truly "leaked" in the user-visible sense. This is a
methodology clarification gate, not a factual error in the page.

